-width: 1px; --bs-card-border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.175); --bs-card-border-radius: 0.375rem; --bs-card-inner-border-radius: calc(0.375rem - (1px)); --bs-card-cap-padding-y: 0.75rem; --bs-card-cap-padding-x: 1.5rem; --bs-card-cap-bg: rgba(33,37,41, 0.03); --bs-card-bg: #fff; --bs-card-img-overlay-padding: 1.5rem; --bs-card-group-margin: 0.75rem; height: 269px; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1) 0px 6px 20px; padding: 1.5rem; -webkit-box-pack: justify !important;\"><div class=\"flex-grow-1 text-center\" style=\"-webkit-box-flex: 1 !important;\"><a class=\"d-inline-block rounded-circle\" href=\"https://www.springboard.com/success/kelly-hart\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none; width: 125px; height: 125px; overflow: hidden;\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/springboard-images/image/upload/v1629203193/Student%20Success/Kelly_Hart_125x125.png\" alt=\"Kelly Hart\" style=\"max-width: 170px; height: 125px; object-fit: contain;\"></a><div>Kelly Hart</div><div>UX/UI Designer at Perficient</div></div><div><a class=\"btn btn-primary mx-auto\" href=\"https://www.springboard.com/success/kelly-hart\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); --bs-btn-padding-y: 0.375rem; --bs-btn-font-size: 1rem; --bs-btn-font-weight: 400; --bs-btn-line-height: 1.5; --bs-btn-color: #fff; --bs-btn-bg: #5e0bd1; --bs-btn-border-width: 1px; --bs-btn-border-color: #5e0bd1; --bs-btn-border-radius: 0.375rem; --bs-btn-hover-border-color: #4b09a7; --bs-btn-box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15),0 1px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.075); --bs-btn-disabled-opacity: 0.65; --bs-btn-focus-box-shadow: 0 0 0 0.25rem rgba(118,48,216, .5); padding: calc(-1px + 0.375rem) calc(-1px + 0.75rem); font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 14px;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" line-height:=\"\" 1.5;=\"\" border-color:=\"\" rgb(94,=\"\" 11,=\"\" 209);=\"\" border-style:=\"\" solid;=\"\" border-width:=\"\" 1px;=\"\" border-image:=\"\" none=\"\" 100%=\"\" 1=\"\" 0=\"\" stretch;=\"\" border-radius:=\"\" 4px;=\"\" background:=\"\" --bs-btn-hover-color:=\"\" #fff;=\"\" --bs-btn-hover-bg:=\"\" #5009b2;=\"\" --bs-btn-focus-shadow-rgb:=\"\" 118,48,216;=\"\" --bs-btn-active-color:=\"\" --bs-btn-active-bg:=\"\" #4b09a7;=\"\" --bs-btn-active-border-color:=\"\" #47089d;=\"\" --bs-btn-active-shadow:=\"\" inset=\"\" 3px=\"\" 5px=\"\" rgba(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0.125);=\"\" --bs-btn-disabled-color:=\"\" --bs-btn-disabled-bg:=\"\" #5e0bd1;=\"\" --bs-btn-disabled-border-color:=\"\" #5e0bd1;\"=\"\">Read Story</a></div></div></div></div></div><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h3\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 32px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Product Design Engineer: What Employers Want</h2><div>Here’s what a standard&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.glassdoor.com/Job/florida-mechanical-product-design-engineer-jobs-SRCH_IL.0,7_IS3318_KO8,42.htm\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.glassdoor.com/Job/florida-mechanical-product-design-engineer-jobs-SRCH_IL.0,7_IS3318_KO8,42.htm\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">product design engineer job posting</a>&nbsp;looks like:</div><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\" style=\"margin: 20px auto; display: table; text-align: center; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/product-design-engineer-job-posting.png\" alt=\"product design engineer job posting\" class=\"wp-image-39743\" width=\"698\" height=\"575\" srcset=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/product-design-engineer-job-posting.png 931w, https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/product-design-engineer-job-posting-380x313.png 380w, https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/product-design-engineer-job-posting-380x313.png 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 698px) 100vw, 698px\" style=\"height: 575px; width: 698px;\"></figure><div>When employers look for a product engineer, they are looking for someone who is able to wear a number of hats in one role. The interdisciplinary nature of product design means that you need to be able to show that you can handle the many different aspects of your job description.</div><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h4\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 32px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">How Much Can You Earn as a Product Design Engineer?</h2><div>For a product design engineer, salary ranges may be wide between different industries and different companies. However, it’s a highly rewarding specialty with many opportunities for advancement. The high base salary range for a product design engineer makes it a highly desirable position. Below are a few salary ranges, divided by experience level.</div><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Entry-Level Product Design Engineer</h3><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\" style=\"margin: 20px auto; display: table; text-align: center; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1206\" height=\"273\" src=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/entry-level-product-design-engineer-average-salary.png\" alt=\"Entry-Level Product Design Engineer average salary\" class=\"wp-image-39745\" srcset=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/entry-level-product-design-engineer-average-salary.png 1206w, https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/entry-level-product-design-engineer-average-salary-380x86.png 380w, https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/entry-level-product-design-engineer-average-salary-380x86.png 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1206px) 100vw, 1206px\" style=\"height: auto;\"></figure><div>The average salary for an entry-level product design engineer is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.payscale.com/research/US/Job=Product_Design_Engineer/Salary/8226c47b/Entry-Level\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">$62,600</a>.</div><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Mid-Level Product Design Engineer</h3><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\" style=\"margin: 20px auto; display: table; text-align: center; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1207\" height=\"281\" src=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/mid-level-product-design-engineer-average-salary.png\" alt=\"Mid-Level Product Design Engineer average salary\" class=\"wp-image-39748\" srcset=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/mid-level-product-design-engineer-average-salary.png 1207w, https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/mid-level-product-design-engineer-average-salary-380x88.png 380w, https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/mid-level-product-design-engineer-average-salary-380x88.png 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1207px) 100vw, 1207px\" style=\"height: auto;\"></figure><div>The average salary for a mid-level product design engineer is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.payscale.com/research/US/Job=Product_Design_Engineer/Salary\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">$73,400</a>.</div><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Senior Product Design Engineer</h3><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\" style=\"color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1207\" height=\"277\" src=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/senior-product-design-engineer-average-salary.png\" alt=\"Senior Product Design Engineer average salary\" class=\"wp-image-39750\" srcset=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/senior-product-design-engineer-average-salary.png 1207w, https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/senior-product-design-engineer-average-salary-380x87.png 380w, https://www.springboard.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/senior-product-design-engineer-average-salary-380x87.png 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1207px) 100vw, 1207px\" style=\"height: auto;\"></figure><div>The average salary for a senior product design engineer is about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.payscale.com/research/US/Job=Senior_Product_Designer/Salary\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">$124,600</a>.</div><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h5\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 32px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Where Can You Find Product Design Engineering Jobs?</h2><div>There are several different ways to find a product engineering job. Here are a few of the most common:</div><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Job Boards</h3><div>When it comes to landing a job, applying frequently and strategically is one of the best ways to ensure you find a job that meets your needs and allows you to work in an environment where you thrive. Some of the major job boards include:</div><h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 22px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><a href=\"https://www.indeed.com/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">Indeed</a></h4><div>Indeed is a job board for jobs of all categories. Finding a job through Indeed can be as simple as customizing a job search and applying to job postings.</div><h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 22px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">LinkedIn</a></h4><div>By using LinkedIn, you can utilize both your network and your resume/portfolio to find a job.</div><h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 22px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><a href=\"https://dribbble.com/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">Dribbble</a></h4><div>This design-specific site showcases portfolios, educational opportunities, and jobs and specializes in helping designers find jobs.</div><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Network</h3><div>Networking has been repeatedly proven to be the best way to find a satisfying job. Building up your network over time can help you to find collaborative projects and new job opportunities that a simple job search won’t. Utilizing your social networks and professional networks to find a job is considered one of the best ways to find a satisfying role where you can grow.</div><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Online Communities</h3><div>By finding online communities, you will be able to explore what specific roles interest you within product design. These communities are also spaces for networking and can help you to make valuable connections within the product design world.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cadcrowd.com/forum/categories\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">CAD crowd</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.productdesignforums.com/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">Product Design Forums</a>&nbsp;are two communities that you should definitely check out.</div><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h6\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 32px; font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">FAQs About Becoming a Product Design Engineer</h2><div>These are a few of the most commonly asked questions about becoming a product design engineer.</div><div id=\"rank-math-faq\" class=\"rank-math-block\" style=\"color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-family: \" haffer=\"\" xh\",=\"\" -apple-system,=\"\" blinkmacsystemfont,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><div class=\"rank-math-list \"><div id=\"faq-question-1671068096014\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\"><h3 class=\"rank-math-question \" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px;\">Is Product Design Engineering a Good Career?</h3><div class=\"rank-math-answer \"><div>Product design engineers&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.careerexplorer.com/careers/industrial-designer/satisfaction/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">rate their job satisfaction</a>&nbsp;as above average. Designers who enjoy building complex projects and have a strong capacity for visual creativity and technical understanding will find the job a rewarding career.</div></div></div><div id=\"faq-question-1671068111270\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\"><h3 class=\"rank-math-question \" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px;\">Can You Become a Product Design Engineer Without a Degree?</h3><div class=\"rank-math-answer \"><div>It is completely possible to become a product design engineer without a degree. The key barriers to entry for product design roles are skills that are not necessarily dependent on your having&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/news/digital-skills-gap-alternative-credentials/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">completed a degree</a>. Job applicants will be asked about many topics, with practical experience and job-related skills being some of the most important. A candidate’s level of education is not something that makes or breaks an application.</div></div></div><div id=\"faq-question-1671068127275\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\"><h3 class=\"rank-math-question \" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px;\">Does Product Design Engineering Require Coding?</h3><div class=\"rank-math-answer \"><div>While many product design engineers understand at least one&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.springboard.com/blog/software-engineering/best-online-coding-courses/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">programming language</a>, it is not a requirement. As product design engineering is a largely collaborative process between interdisciplinary teams, some technical skills like coding are carried out by programmers on the team and not necessarily the product designer themselves.</div></div></div><div id=\"faq-question-1671068152458\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\"><h3 class=\"rank-math-question \" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: rgb(50, 53, 79); font-size: 26px;\">Does Product Design Engineering Pay Well?</h3><div class=\"rank-math-answer \"><div>Product Design Engineer positions pay well, with the average salary being around&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.glassdoor.com/Salaries/product-design-engineer-salary-SRCH_KO0,23.htm\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(94, 11, 209); text-decoration-line: none;\">$110,000 in the US</a>.</div></div></div></div></div></div>', 6, 6, 1, 'COVER-6818b8a723c957.40606320.jpg', '2025-04-28 14:31:26');
INSERT INTO `post` (`post_id`, `post_title`, `post_text`, `user_id`, `category`, `publish`, `cover_url`, `created_at`) VALUES
(30, 'How to choose the best Gmail client: Top 5 picks!', '<div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><div>For most of us, Gmail is the go-to platform for managing everyday emails. The reason? Its default interface is straightforward and something we’re used to. Still, it doesn’t always offer the level of customization or advanced efficiency and automation features we need, which can hurt productivity.</div></div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><div><span class=\"contentfulRichText_strong__MaH0M\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">That’s where Gmail clients come in.</span></div></div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><div>The right email client can help you organize your workflow and boost efficiency with modern email management and AI-native features. Some solutions today can automatically generate context-rich responses and even entire emails, so you have a leg up on your day. The only problem is that there are tons of Gmail clients out there—so, how do you find something that’s&nbsp;<i>perfect for you</i>?</div></div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><div>In this article, we’ll discuss the best Gmail clients available. We’ll go over:</div></div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><ul class=\"contentfulRichText_list__89IEM\" style=\"padding-left: 1em; margin: 0.65em 0px; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 20px; font-family: \" lyon=\"\" text\",=\"\" georgia,=\"\" yumincho,=\"\" \"yu=\"\" mincho\",=\"\" \"hiragino=\"\" mincho=\"\" pron\",=\"\" pro\",=\"\" \"songti=\"\" tc\",=\"\" sc\",=\"\" simsun,=\"\" \"nanum=\"\" myeongjo\",=\"\" nanummyeongjo,=\"\" batang,=\"\" serif;=\"\" font-feature-settings:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" oldstyle-nums;\"=\"\"><li class=\"contentfulRichText_listItem___Swmu\" style=\"margin-top: 0.25em; margin-bottom: 0.25em;\"><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; --rich-text-limit-max-width: 700px;\"><div>The benefits of using a Gmail client</div></div></li><li class=\"contentfulRichText_listItem___Swmu\" style=\"margin-top: 0.25em; margin-bottom: 0.25em;\"><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; --rich-text-limit-max-width: 700px;\"><div>Tips to find a suitable solution</div></div></li><li class=\"contentfulRichText_listItem___Swmu\" style=\"margin-top: 0.25em; margin-bottom: 0.25em;\"><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; --rich-text-limit-max-width: 700px;\"><div>Top five options for a Gmail client in 2025</div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><div class=\"contentfulRichText_titleSpacingH2__yu1dl\" id=\"email-client-for-gmail—an-overview\" style=\"padding-top: 4em; position: relative;\"><h2 class=\"title_title__DWL5N title_titleSizeM__e46NM title_titleWeightBold__838EK title_titleFamilyInter__Ra6_Q\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 32px; line-height: 40px; --font-weight-fallback: 700; letter-spacing: -0.75px;\">Email client for Gmail—An overview</h2></div></div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><div>Gmail clients are powerful third-party apps that help users access, manage, and interact with their Gmail accounts outside of the primary web interface. But if Gmail’s web client already works fine,&nbsp;<span class=\"contentfulRichText_strong__MaH0M\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">why even switch to a third-party service</span>?</div></div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><div>Because you’d be missing out on a new era of email efficiency supported by major new functionalities, features, and automation. Third-party clients go beyond convenience—they introduce productivity-boosting features like automation and deeper customization, often AI-assisted, that Gmail simply doesn’t offer. Let’s see how both options differ:</div></div><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" --rich-text-limit-max-width:=\"\" 700px;\"=\"\"><ul class=\"contentfulRichText_list__89IEM\" style=\"padding-left: 1em; margin: 0.65em 0px; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 20px; font-family: \" lyon=\"\" text\",=\"\" georgia,=\"\" yumincho,=\"\" \"yu=\"\" mincho\",=\"\" \"hiragino=\"\" mincho=\"\" pron\",=\"\" pro\",=\"\" \"songti=\"\" tc\",=\"\" sc\",=\"\" simsun,=\"\" \"nanum=\"\" myeongjo\",=\"\" nanummyeongjo,=\"\" batang,=\"\" serif;=\"\" font-feature-settings:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" oldstyle-nums;\"=\"\"><li class=\"contentfulRichText_listItem___Swmu\" style=\"margin-top: 0.25em; margin-bottom: 0.25em;\"><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; --rich-text-limit-max-width: 700px;\"><div><span class=\"contentfulRichText_strong__MaH0M\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Web-based Gmail</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"contentfulRichText_strong__MaH0M\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">client</span>: It is the default interface, accessible through any web browser. It provides a fully integrated Gmail experience and access to all the features Gmail offers, including email organizations, Google Drive integration, etc., though that’s where it also falls short. The web-based Gmail client doesn’t go beyond basic interface and organization on its own and doesn’t offer deep integration with other productivity tools.</div></div></li><li class=\"contentfulRichText_listItem___Swmu\" style=\"margin-top: 0.25em; margin-bottom: 0.25em;\"><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; --rich-text-limit-max-width: 700px;\"><div><span class=\"contentfulRichText_strong__MaH0M\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Third-party email clients</span>: These applications offer additional features, such as better customization, multi-account management, and integration with other work tools to support Gmail accounts. Some email clients are designed with power users in mind, and come equipped with advanced features like smart inbox organization and automated task management that help handle emails efficiently. The main reason users choose these applications is to have a more intelligent and tailored email management experience, as well as enjoy greater control over their inbox and workflow.</div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"contentfulRichTextLayout_rtSpacingS__fOW8p\" style=\"margin: 1.5em auto; color: rgb(25, 25, 24); font-family: NotionInter, Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";\"=\"\"><div class=\"contentfulRichText_bodyLimit__F5GOU\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; max-width: 700px; --rich-text-limit-max-width: 700px;\"><div role=\"button\" class=\"lightbox_lightboxTrigger__pXsqp\" aria-label=\"Open lightbox\" style=\"cursor: zoom-in;\"><figure class=\"mediaWithCaption_figure__Q6RPs\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\"><div class=\"mediaWithCaption_media__TLfag\" style=\"line-height: 0;\"><img alt=\"Source: Gmail\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1633\" height=\"683\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"next-image contentfulAsset_image__cZ0Nl\" srcset=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.ctfassets.net%2Fspoqsaf9291f%2F2Lcl0N6mAVjGDzewqYPTTE%2Fa3271b3f626cb2400b5f1f4372b79128%2FGmail.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.ctfassets.net%2Fspoqsaf9291f%2F2Lcl0N6mAVjGDzewqYPTTE%2Fa3271b3f626cb2400b5f1f4372b79128%2FGmail.png&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"https://www.notion.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.ctfassets.net%2Fspoqsaf9291f%2F2Lcl0N6mAVjGDzewqYPTTE%2Fa3271b3f626cb2400b5f1f4372b79128%2FGmail.png&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75\" style=\"border: 0px; display: block; width: 700px; height: auto; object-fit: cover; color: transparent;\"></div><figcaption class=\"caption_figcaption__nkQ4J\" style=\"display: flex; font-size: 15px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.66); margin-top: 10px; cursor: default; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between;\"><div>Source: Gmail</div><div class=\"caption_lightboxButtonWrap__tDGsz\" style=\"flex-grow: 0; margin-left: 20px;\"><button class=\"caption_lightboxButton__drWUP\" aria-label=\"View image in a Lightbox\" style=\"font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; 